  "title": "Academic Affairs",
  "description": "Jointly established by New York University and East China Normal University, NYU Shanghai is the third degree-granting campus in NYU’s global network, joining NYU Abu Dhabi and NYU's campus in New York City.",
  "language": "en",
  "published_time": "",
  "modified_time": "",
  "sitemap_lastmod": null,
  "text": "Academic Affairs\nAcademic Affairs supports NYU Shanghai’s community of scholars, its shared ideals, and core values. Together with the University’s Deans, Area Heads, and Directors, Academic Affairs provides opportunities, infrastructure, and resources to encourage and enable faculty and students to meet the rigorous demands of an NYU Shanghai education and pursue their finest work.\nAcademic Affairs' main responsibilities include academic advising, academic skills building, and academic support for students, governance of academic policies and processes, supporting curricular innovation and teaching excellence, and developing learning opportunities for students inside and outside of the classroom as well as within the NYU Global Network.\nJohn Robertson Vice Provost for Academic Affairs\nMeet the Team\nAcademic Services\nAcademic Advising\nPrograms and Events\nAcademic Procedures\nStudy Away\nMeet the Advisors\nAcademic Operations\nNYU Shanghai Textbook\nUndergraduate Research Symposium\nAdministrative Support For Teaching\nAcademic Resource Center\nTutoring Services\nARC Workshops\nAcademic Handouts\nAcademic Accommodations\nCommunity-Engaged Learning\nService-learning Courses\nImmersive-learning Trips\nCenter for Teaching and Learning\nCTL Program & Upcoming Events\nCTL Services\nTeaching Resources\nCurriculum & Teaching\nCore Curriculum\nAssessment and Accreditation\nAcademic Integrity and Grade Appeals\nAcademic Program Review\nGlobal Awards\nGlobal Awards News\nGlobal Awards Programs\nExplore Awards and Fellowships\nStudy Away Program\nIncoming Study Away\nOutgoing Study Away\nNYU Global Network\nSpecial Programs\nJanuary Term\nSummer Term\nSummer Chinese\nLanguage Immersion Program\nAcademic Highlights\nBig Brothers Big Sisters Program\nCollege and Career Lab in Summer\nDeans' Undergraduate Research Fund (DURF)\nNYU Shanghai Reads\nUndergraduate Research Symposium\nView Academic Affairs Weekly Newsletter",
